 BY BAMIDELE FAMOOFO The management of Egbin Power Plc, has announced the resumption of operations at the plant following the recent fire incident at the Power Plant which was immediately contained. “Unit (ST05) was put back in service and synchronized to the national grid at 19:57 hours on 4th February and is back on stream with a capacity of 220mw,” a statement from the company said. “The Technical team at the plant is working tirelessly to ensure that 660mw is added to the grid before the weekend runs out. Egbin continues to work with the regulatory authorities and other stakeholders to achieve full restoration in line with global health, safety, and environmental standards.” The company expressed gratitude to its employees, the public, partners and stakeholders for their unwavering support, cooperation and understanding. “We use this medium to reiterate our commitment to bringing energy to life responsibly through safe, innovative and sustainable power generation,” it stated. 